cus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_3617413\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 11, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104zml1665702632238.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/zml1665702632238.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/zml1665702632238.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"zml1665702632238\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Switch Palette (\n                              SwitchPalette)\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">This property determines whether the image's own color palette is used, or whether the current palette, which may be determined elsewhere, is used. <code class=\"ph codeph\">True</code> or <code class=\"ph codeph defvalue\">False</code> (default).\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zml1665702632238__p_d107402e1_d107403e1_d107404e1\">SwitchPalette<code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code><code class=\"ph codeph\">\"</code><code class=\"ph codeph\">True</code> | <code class=\"ph codeph defvalue\">False</code><code class=\"ph codeph\">\"</code></p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"zml1665702632238__table_d12659e1_d12660e1_d12661e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"zml1665702632238__table_d12659e1_d12660e1_d12661e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Value</p>\n</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"zml1665702632238__table_d12659e1_d12660e1_d12661e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Description</p>\n</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zml1665702632238__table_d12659e1_d12660e1_d12661e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">True</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zml1665702632238__table_d12659e1_d12660e1_d12661e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">The display palette is switched to the picture's palette when the picture gets focus.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zml1665702632238__table_d12659e1_d12660e1_d12661e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph defvalue\">False</code> (Default)</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zml1665702632238__table_d12659e1_d12660e1_d12661e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">The picture is displayed using the current palette. This can be the palette from another application, picture, or a uniform palette.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"zml1665702632238__section_byc_jqy_zwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d620497e141\">Picture</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zml1665702632238__p_d107408e1_d107409e1_d107410e1\">The <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Switch Palette</span> property\n            is only applicable if the display hardware is palette-based (most 256-color systems use\n            a palette) and the picture carries a palette with non-standard colors (256-color\n            pictures).</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"zml1665702632238__section_ixj_kqy_zwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d620497e153\">Command Button</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zml1665702632238__p_d107414e1_d107415e1_d107416e1\">For command buttons, this property is supported\n            only when <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Representation</span> is set to <code class=\"ph codeph\">Uniface</code>.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"zml1665702632238__section_kcb_mqy_zwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d620497e168\">Example: Setting in ProcScript</h2>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"zml1665702632238__pre_sk2_nqy_zwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">$fieldproperties(FLD) = \"switchpalette=true\"</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"zml1665702632238__section_vqc_4qy_zwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d620497e178\">Applies To</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"zml1665702632238__ul_tcp_4qy_zwb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"zml1665702632238__li_d42248e1_d42249e1_d42250e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zml1665702632238__p_d107423e1_d107424e1_d107425e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rgn1665702634165.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rgn1665702634165.html\" title=\"Image to use as the background image on the map widget.\">Image Name</a>\n</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"zml1665702632238__li_d42251e1_d42252e1_d42253e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zml1665702632238__p_d107426e1_d107427e1_d107428e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jrc1665702631553.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jrc1665702631553.html\" title=\"The CommandButton is a logical widget that enables a user to initiate an action by clicking the button.\">CommandButton</a>\n</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/btj1665702631955.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Representation</a><p>This property determines the appearance of the command button when running on the Microsoft Windows operating system (XP and later versions). One of Windows (default), Uniface, or Header.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3617413\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3617413\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Switch Palette ( SwitchPalette) Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 11, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Switch Palette ( SwitchPalette) This property determines whether the image's own color palette is used, or whether the current palette, which may be determined elsewhere, is used. True or False (default). SwitchPalette = \" True | False \" Value Description True The display palette is switched to the picture's palette when the picture gets focus. False (Default) The picture is displayed using the current palette. This can be the palette from another application, picture, or a uniform palette. Picture The Switch Palette property is only applicable if the display hardware is palette-based (most 256-color systems use a palette) and the picture carries a palette with non-standard colors (256-color pictures). Command Button For command buttons, this property is supported only when Representation is set to Uniface . Example: Setting in ProcScript $fieldproperties(FLD) = \"switchpalette=true\" Copy Applies To Image Name CommandButton Related Links Representation This property determines the appearance of the command button when running on the Microsoft Windows operating system (XP and later versions). One of Windows (default), Uniface, or Header. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}